deral Aviation Act of 1958 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/726"},"text":"Public Law 85–726","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/779"},"text":"72 Stat. 779","children":[],"tail":") is retained on authority of 49:106(g). The words “modifying”, “modify”, and “modified” are omitted as surplus."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a), the words “airman holding a certificate issued under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s44703"},"text":"section 44703 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” are substituted for “civil airman” for clarity."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(1), before subclause (A), the words “certificate issued under this chapter” are substituted for “type certificate, production certificate, airworthiness certificate, airman certificate, air carrier operating certificate, air navigation facility certificate (including airport operating certificate), or air agency certificate” to eliminate unnecessary words.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(2), the words “in his discretion” and “regarding the use or operation of an aircraft” in 49 App.:1429(b) are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (c), the words “cases of” in 49 App.:1429(a) are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(1), before clause (A), the word “adversely” is substituted for “whose certificate is” in 49 App.:1429(a), and the words “an opportunity for a” are added, for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the United States Code. The words “of the FAA” in 49 App.:1431(e) are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(2), the words “consistent with this subsection” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(3), the word “Administrator” is substituted for “Federal Aviation Administration” because of 49:106(b) and (g).","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e), before clause (1), the words “the effectiveness of” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcbfe0478-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcbfe0479-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/254"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–254","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as par. (1), inserted heading, and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2012—Subsec. (d)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/153"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–153","children":[],"tail":" struck out “but is bound by all validly adopted interpretations of laws and regulations the Administrator carries out and of written agency policy guidance available to the public related to sanctions to be imposed under this section unless the Board finds an interpretation is arbitrary, capricious, or otherwise not according to law” after “Administrator”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/176"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–176","children":[],"tail":" inserted “design organization, production certificate holder,” after “appliance,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181","children":[],"tail":" amended heading and text of subsec. (e) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “When a person files an appeal with the Board under subsection (d) of the section, the order of the Administrator is stayed. However, if the Administrator advises the Board that an emergency exists and safety in air commerce or air transportation requires the order to be effective immediately—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) the order is effective; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) the Board shall make a final disposition of the appeal not later than 60 days after the Administrator so advises the Board.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idcbfe047a-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcbfe047b-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2003 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/176"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–176","children":[],"tail":" applicable only to fiscal years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 2003","children":[],"tail":", except as otherwise specifically provided, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/176/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 108–176","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s106"},"text":"section 106 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idcbfe047c-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2000 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–181","children":[],"tail":" applicable only to fiscal years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1999","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/181/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 106–181","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s106"},"text":"section 106 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idcbfe047d-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Risk Model for Production Facility Inspections","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/63/tIII/s314"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–63, title III, § 314","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-05-16"},"text":"May 16, 2024","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/138/1077"},"text":"138 Stat. 1077","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/118/63/tIII/s314"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"In General","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 12 months after the date of enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2024-05-16"},"text":"May 16, 2024","children":[],"tail":"], and periodically thereafter, the Administrator [of the Federal Aviation Administration] shall—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" conduct a review of the risk-based model used by certification management offices of the FAA [Federal Aviation Administration] to inform the frequency of aircraft manufacturing or production facility inspections; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" update the model to ensure such model adequately accounts for risk at facilities during periods of increased production.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Briefings","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 60 days after the date on which the review is completed under subsection (a), the Administrator shall brief the appropriate committees of Congress [Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation of the Senate and Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure of the House of Representatives] on—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the results of the review;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any changes made to the risk-based model described in subsection (a); and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" how such changes would help improve the in-plant inspection process.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
